Note:
ARC counters smoke test - regression guard for the .data-cell codegen pattern.

This test verifies that top-level `Let X be 0` declarations combined with
`Set X to ...` statements inside Processes compile to a real .data cell
with proper leaq/movq memory reads and stores. This is the same pattern
arc_utils.runa uses for its statistics counters
(arc_total_allocations, arc_total_retains, arc_total_releases, etc.).

The pattern is correct under the current bootstrap codegen because
codegen_build_mutated_globals (codegen.runa:96-134) detects Set statements
that target a top-level Let and promotes the variable to a memory-backed
mutable global. The variable-load and lvalue-address paths then route
through leaq + movq instead of inlining the literal initializer.

The companion pattern in console.runa - `Constant GLOBAL_CONSOLE_PTR is 0`
combined with `memory_set_int64(GLOBAL_CONSOLE_PTR, 0, v)` - did NOT
trigger that promotion because the parser sees Constant rather than Let
and codegen treats the symbol as a compile-time literal at every use site.
That mismatch was the cause of DEV-LOG #115's NULL-deref segfault. This
smoke test does NOT cover the Constant case (that pattern is correctly
broken at the codegen level and the fix was to delete the cache entirely);
it covers the working Let-based pattern that arc_utils.runa relies on.

If a future codegen change silently regresses the mutable-globals lowering,
the assertions below will fire and pinpoint the failure.

Exit codes (encoded so a CI runner can identify which assertion failed):
  0    All assertions passed.
  10   Local counter did not initialize to expected starting value.
  11   Local counter did not retain Set value across reads.
  12   Local counter did not increment correctly under read-modify-write.
  13   Local counter cross-cell aliasing detected (two cells share storage).
  14   arc_get_stats_allocations did not return 0 after arc_stats_reset.
  15   arc_get_stats_retains did not return 0 after arc_stats_reset.
  16   arc_get_stats_releases did not return 0 after arc_stats_reset.
  17   arc_get_stats_live_objects did not return 0 after arc_stats_reset.
  18   arc_get_stats_peak_objects did not return 0 after arc_stats_reset.
  19   arc_get_stats_deallocations did not return 0 after arc_stats_reset.
  20   Second arc_stats_reset cycle did not re-zero counters.
:End Note

Import "runtime/stdlib/arc/arc_utils.runa" as ArcUtils

Note: Local top-level Let cells - same pattern as arc_utils.runa lines 52-60.
Note: These cells exercise the codegen path directly without depending on the
Note: arc_heap subsystem, so a failure here pinpoints the codegen regression
Note: independently of any arc_heap or layout-allocator issue.
Let smoke_counter_a be 0
Let smoke_counter_b be 0
Let smoke_counter_c be 0

Process called "mutate_local_counters" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning:
        Goal: exercise the read-modify-write path of all three local counters
        in sequence to verify that (a) each cell holds its own storage, (b)
        the .data cell survives across Process boundaries, and (c) the
        increment idiom `Set X to X plus N` lowers to the expected leaq+movq
        pair. Returns the sum of the three counters so the caller can verify
        the final values without exposing the cells directly.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation:
        Steps:
            1. Set smoke_counter_a to 100 (raw assignment).
            2. Set smoke_counter_b to 200 (raw assignment).
            3. Set smoke_counter_c to smoke_counter_a plus smoke_counter_b
               (cross-cell read-modify-write).
            4. Add 1 to smoke_counter_a five times (in-place increment loop).
            5. Return the sum of all three cells.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints:
        Six writes, ten reads. No allocation, no syscalls. Loop body is
        trivial; total runtime is dominated by function call overhead.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope:
        Operates only on this file's private top-level Lets. No caller input.
        No pointer dereference. No allocator interaction.
    @End Security_Scope

    Set smoke_counter_a to 100
    Set smoke_counter_b to 200
    Set smoke_counter_c to smoke_counter_a plus smoke_counter_b

    Let i be 0
    While i is less than 5:
        Set smoke_counter_a to smoke_counter_a plus 1
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While

    Let total be smoke_counter_a plus smoke_counter_b
    Set total to total plus smoke_counter_c
    Return total
End Process

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning:
        Goal: run a sequence of assertions against the .data-cell behavior of
        top-level Let declarations and against arc_utils.runa's statistics
        counters. Each assertion returns a distinct exit code on failure so
        a regression can be diagnosed without re-running individual cases.
        Exit 0 indicates every assertion passed.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation:
        Steps:
            1. Verify the three local cells initialize to 0 at program start
               (proves zero-initialization of .data section worked).
            2. Verify Set persists across Process calls by writing then
               reading each cell.
            3. Verify cross-cell independence by writing to one and reading
               another (catches aliasing bugs in the global table).
            4. Verify read-modify-write increment via mutate_local_counters
               and compare the returned total against the expected value.
            5. Call arc_stats_reset and verify each of the six public stats
               getters returns 0 (proves the arc_utils.runa cells lower
               correctly).
            6. Call arc_stats_reset a second time and re-verify, proving the
               cells are durable across multiple reset cycles.
            7. Return 0 on success.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints:
        O(1) work. No allocation. The arc_stats_reset call does nine Set
        statements; each getter does one load. Total execution time is a
        handful of microseconds.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope:
        Operates only on this file's locals plus arc_utils.runa's public
        getters and arc_stats_reset, all of which are statistics-only
        functions with no caller-controlled pointer arguments. No allocator
        or syscall surface is exercised.
    @End Security_Scope

    Note: Assertion 1: zero-initialization.
    If smoke_counter_a is not equal to 0:
        Return 10
    End If
    If smoke_counter_b is not equal to 0:
        Return 10
    End If
    If smoke_counter_c is not equal to 0:
        Return 10
    End If

    Note: Assertion 2 / 3 / 4: Set/read/increment behavior via mutate_local_counters.
    Note: After mutate: a=105, b=200, c=300, total=605.
    Let total be proc mutate_local_counters
    If total is not equal to 605:
        Return 12
    End If
    If smoke_counter_a is not equal to 105:
        Return 11
    End If
    If smoke_counter_b is not equal to 200:
        Return 11
    End If
    If smoke_counter_c is not equal to 300:
        Return 11
    End If

    Note: Assertion 5: cross-cell aliasing. Write a distinctive value to one
    Note: cell and verify the others are unchanged.
    Set smoke_counter_a to 999
    If smoke_counter_b is not equal to 200:
        Return 13
    End If
    If smoke_counter_c is not equal to 300:
        Return 13
    End If

    Note: Assertion 6: arc_utils counters zero after reset.
    proc arc_stats_reset from ArcUtils

    Let a be proc arc_get_stats_allocations from ArcUtils
    If a is not equal to 0:
        Return 14
    End If

    Let r be proc arc_get_stats_retains from ArcUtils
    If r is not equal to 0:
        Return 15
    End If

    Let rel be proc arc_get_stats_releases from ArcUtils
    If rel is not equal to 0:
        Return 16
    End If

    Let live be proc arc_get_stats_live_objects from ArcUtils
    If live is not equal to 0:
        Return 17
    End If

    Let peak be proc arc_get_stats_peak_objects from ArcUtils
    If peak is not equal to 0:
        Return 18
    End If

    Let dealloc be proc arc_get_stats_deallocations from ArcUtils
    If dealloc is not equal to 0:
        Return 19
    End If

    Note: Assertion 7: second reset cycle also re-zeroes.
    proc arc_stats_reset from ArcUtils

    Let a2 be proc arc_get_stats_allocations from ArcUtils
    If a2 is not equal to 0:
        Return 20
    End If

    Let r2 be proc arc_get_stats_retains from ArcUtils
    If r2 is not equal to 0:
        Return 20
    End If

    Note: All assertions passed.
    Return 0
End Process
